X-PIE: High-Confidence Crosslink Curation (x-pie-curation.py)
================================================================================

Version: 1.0
License: MIT
DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.20523994

X-PIE curation is a computational pipeline for filtering, validating, and
annotating pLink crosslinking mass spectrometry (XL-MS) results to produce
high-confidence protein-protein interaction (PPI) datasets. It integrates
external databases (STRING, UniProt, RCSB PDB) to distinguish known interactions
from novel candidates and identify structural support for unreported PPIs.

