================================================================================
1. OVERVIEW
================================================================================

X-PIE curation performs automated quality control and database annotation of
XL-MS results through the following steps:

    Step 1: Load pLink search results
    Step 2: Filter inter-protein crosslink PSMs by FDR
    Step 3: Resolve protein pairs and crosslinked site pairs
    Step 4: Apply site-pair count threshold
    Step 5: Write curated XL-MS summary files
    Step 6: Evaluate PPIs against STRING database
    Step 7: Search homologous PDB structures for unreported PPIs

The pipeline is implemented as a single Python script (x-pie-curation.py) with
both interactive (recommended for first-time users) and non-interactive modes.


================================================================================
2. DEPENDENCIES
================================================================================

The script requires Python 3 and the following packages. The versions listed
have been tested and confirmed to operate normally.

| Package     | Version | Purpose                              |
|-------------|---------|--------------------------------------|
| pandas      | 2.3.1   | Data manipulation and CSV parsing      |
| numpy       | 1.26.4  | Numerical operations                 |
| requests    | 2.32.3  | HTTP requests for web APIs             |
| biopython   | 1.85    | Sequence alignment and PDB parsing   |

Check availability before running:

    python x-pie-curation.py --check-deps

If any packages are missing, install via pip:

    pip install pandas numpy requests biopython

External Web Services (internet required for Steps 6-7):
--------------------------------------------------------

| Service     | URL                              | Purpose                         |
|-------------|----------------------------------|---------------------------------|
| UniProt     | https://rest.uniprot.org         | Protein sequence and taxonomy   |
| STRING      | https://string-db.org            | Protein interaction network     |
| RCSB PDB    | https://search.rcsb.org          | Protein structure database      |

At startup, the workflow checks Internet access to UniProt, STRING, and RCSB PDB.
- If all three services are reachable, the workflow continues normally.
- If internet access is unavailable, the program prints: `Internet connection is required for STRING and PDB annotation`
- In interactive mode, you can then choose to:
  - exit immediately
  - continue with local XL-MS filtering only and skip STRING/PDB annotation


