3. QUICK START
================================================================================

3.1 Prepare Input Files

Place your pLink result CSV file(s) in a folder:

    ./input/
    └── plink_results.csv

3.2 Run the Pipeline

Interactive mode (recommended for first-time users):

    python x-pie-curation.py

Non-interactive mode:

    python x-pie-curation.py --non-interactive --input-dir ./input --output-dir ./output

3.3 Review Outputs

Check the curated PPI lists in output/ and use them for downstream modeling
with x-pie-modeling.py.


================================================================================
4. INPUT FILES
================================================================================

4.1 pLink Result CSV File(s)

The script accepts either a single CSV file or a folder containing multiple
pLink result CSV files.

Required columns:

| Column       | Description                          | Expected Values          |
|--------------|--------------------------------------|--------------------------|
| Peptide_Type | Peptide type code                    | 3 or "cross-link"        |
| Protein_Type | Protein type code                    | 2 or "inter-protein"     |
| Score        | pLink search score                   | Numeric                  |
| Target_Decoy | Target/decoy label                   | 2 (target-target)        |
| Q-value      | FDR q-value                          | Numeric, 0-1             |
| Proteins     | Protein pair annotation string       | See format below         |

4.2 Protein Annotation Format

The Proteins column must contain entries in one of these formats:

    sp|P12345|PROT1(100)-sp|P67890|PROT2(200)
    P12345(100)-P67890(200)

Where:
- P12345, P67890 are UniProt accessions
- 100, 200 are crosslinked residue positions (lysine NZ sites)

If multiple candidate pairs are listed in one row (separated by "/"), the
script selects the most frequent pair across the entire dataset.

Important:
Ensure your pLink export includes all required columns. Missing columns will
cause the script to exit with an error.


================================================================================
5. WORKFLOW
================================================================================

Step 1: Load pLink Result Files
-------------------------------
Input:  pLink CSV file(s) from --input-dir
Output: Console summary of files loaded and total row count

The script reads one or more pLink result CSV files. If a folder is given,
all CSV files are merged. Required columns are validated.

Step 2: Filter Inter-Protein Crosslink PSMs
-----------------------------------------
Input:  Merged pLink results, --fdr threshold
Output: Filtered target-target (TT) inter-protein PSMs

Retains only crosslink PSMs (Peptide_Type == 3) that are inter-protein
(Protein_Type == 2) with Q-value <= FDR threshold.

Step 3: Resolve PPIs and XL Site Pairs
-------------------------------------
Input:  Filtered inter-protein PSMs
Output: Unique XL site pairs and PPI table

Parses the Proteins column to extract protein accessions and crosslinked
residue positions. Resolves ambiguous site pairs by frequency voting. 

Step 4: Apply Site-Pair Count Threshold
---------------------------------------
Input:  Site pairs and PPI table, --min-site-pairs
Output: Retained high-confidence PPIs

Filters PPIs by requiring at least a minimum number of unique crosslinked
site pairs per protein pair.

Step 5: Write XL-MS Summary Files
--------------------------------
Input:  Retained PPIs and site pairs
Output: output/PPI.dat, output/PPI_XL_Sites.dat

Writes the curated PPI list and corresponding crosslinked residue pairs.

Step 6: Evaluate PPIs Against STRING
-------------------------------------
Input:  Retained PPIs, --string-required-score
Output: output/Reported_PPI.dat, output/Unreported_PPI.dat

Queries the STRING database for each PPI:
- Detects species from UniProt accessions via UniProt REST API
- Maps accessions to STRING identifiers
- Fetches interaction network and classifies as "reported" or "unreported"

Step 7: Search Homologous PDB Structures
----------------------------------------
Input:  Unreported PPIs, --identity-threshold
Output: output/PDB_homology_results.dat

For unreported PPIs, searches RCSB PDB for homologous structures:
- Fetches full sequences from UniProt
- Queries RCSB PDB for entries containing both sequences
- Performs local pairwise alignment to calculate identity
- Retains only pairs where both proteins exceed the identity threshold


================================================================================
6. CONFIGURATION
================================================================================

6.1 Command-Line Arguments

| Argument                | Default   | Description                                    |
|-------------------------|-----------|------------------------------------------------|
| --input-dir             | ./input   | Input CSV file or folder containing pLink CSVs |
| --output-dir            | ./output  | Output directory                               |
| --fdr                   | 1.0       | FDR threshold (%)                              |
| --min-site-pairs        | 1         | Minimum unique XL site pairs per PPI           |
| --string-score-shreshold  | 0         | Minimum STRING combined score (0-1)         |
| --identity-threshold    | 30.0      | Homologous PDB identity threshold (%)          |
| --network-failure-mode  | False     |  Running mode when network connection is unavailable: choose to exit  |

6.2 Mode Behavior

+------------------+---------------+------------------+
| Invocation       | Config Source | Interactive?     |
+------------------+---------------+------------------+
| (no args)        | Defaults      | Yes              |
| --non-interactive| CLI arguments | No               |
+------------------+---------------+------------------+

In interactive mode, the script prompts you to confirm or override each
parameter. In non-interactive mode, all parameters are taken from CLI arguments.

6.3 Example Commands

Interactive mode:

    python x-pie-curation.py

Non-interactive mode with custom parameters:

python xlms_ppi_evaluation.py --non-interactive \
    --input-dir ./input \
    --output-dir ./output \
    --fdr 1 \
    --min-site-pairs 1 \
    --string-score-shreshold 0.7 \
    --identity-threshold 30
    --network-failure-mode  local-only(exit)

