================================================================================
8. TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

Problem: Missing columns error
    Solution: Check that your pLink CSV export contains all required columns:
              Peptide_Type, Protein_Type, Score, Target_Decoy, Q-value,
              Proteins.

Problem: No rows after filtering
    Solution: Your FDR threshold may be too strict. Try increasing --fdr.
              Verify that Target_Decoy == 2 (target-target) is present.

Problem: No valid protein/site pairs
    Solution: Check the Proteins column format. Expected patterns:
              sp|ACCESSION|NAME(SITE)-sp|ACCESSION|NAME(SITE)
              ACCESSION(SITE)-ACCESSION(SITE)

Problem: STRING step fails
    Solution: Check your internet connection. Verify that your accessions are
              valid UniProt IDs. If most fail to map, check species detection.

Problem: PDB step fails or hangs
    Solution: This step queries external APIs and requires stable internet.
              For large numbers of unreported PPIs, expect 10+ minutes.
              If RCSB search fails repeatedly, try again later.

Problem: Biopython alignment errors
    Solution: Ensure biopython >= 1.85 is installed. For large sequences,
              memory issues may occur; try processing fewer PPIs at a time.


